text:
Hi All,

I am trying to create a schema using Postman against the endpoint `/crm/v3/schemas` that has the following bool property:
```{
      "name": "is_published",
      "label": "Is Published",
      "type": "bool",
      "fieldType": "bool",
}```
Against this, I am getting an error:
```{
    "status": "error",
    "message": "Boolean properties must have exactly two options; one with a value of 'true', the other with a value of 'false'. Property 'is_published' of object type 'sweepstakes_test_1' has more than two options",
    "correlationId": "cd2c945f-deea-4d35-b07f-5d8e0bd0fcd8",
    "context": {
        "property": [
            "is_published"
        ],
        "objectTypeId": [
            "sweepstakes_test_1"
        ]
    },
    "category": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
    "subCategory": "PropertyValidationError.INVALID_BOOLEAN_OPTION"
}```

With any type of property that requires options to choose from you need to add those options when creating the property.  In the case of a boolean it requires two options, something like:

"options":
[
	{
		"label":"True",
		"value":"true"
	},
	{
		"label":"False",
		"value":"false"
	}
]

Hi,
the url seems to be fine!
I tried different things, but couldn't figure out why it's returning 404.

Maybe try version 4 of the api
```<https://api.hubapi.com/crm/v4/objects/contacts/XXXXXXX/associations/notes>```
If it's also not working, you can also try to load via the batch route - make sure to use POST instead of GET

```url = "<https://api.hubapi.com/crm/v4/associations/contacts/notes/batch/read>"

payload = json.dumps({
  "inputs": [
    { "id": "XXXXXXX" },
    { "id": "YYYYYYY" }
  ]
})
headers = {
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Authorization': f'Bearer {access_token}'
}

response = requests.request("POST", url, headers=headers, data=payload)```
